# Pabna municipal CMS stack

## Architecture

- **Backend**: Laravel 11. All HTTP routes and authorization live in `routes/web.php` (and `routes/auth.php`). Use Eloquent for every database read/write; **never** connect the browser directly to the database.
- **Frontend**: Inertia.js + React in `resources/js/Pages`. React is the view layer only; data arrives as props from controllers.
- **Legacy UI**: The old TanStack Start app is archived under `legacy/tanstack-start/` for porting layouts and copy into Inertia pages.

## Development (Docker)

- `docker compose up -d` starts PHP-FPM (`app`) and Nginx. The `app` service loads `.env` via `env_file` so `DB_*` is visible to PHP and to the entrypoint wait loop. Compose sets `SESSION_DRIVER=file`, `CACHE_STORE=file`, and `QUEUE_CONNECTION=sync` so sessions/cache/jobs do not hit the DB unless you choose `database` drivers.
- **MySQL 8 (Docker)**: copy `.env.example` to `.env` (defaults target MySQL), then `docker compose --profile mysql up -d`. Use `DB_HOST=mysql` and credentials matching the `mysql` service (`MYSQL_*` in compose). Run `docker compose exec app php artisan migrate`. The PHP entrypoint waits until MySQL accepts TCP connections before starting FPM.
- **SQLite (no MySQL container)**: set `DB_CONNECTION=sqlite` in `.env`; DB file at `database/database.sqlite`. SQLite uses `journal_mode=DELETE` by default in `config/database.php` so WAL sidecars are optional; the entrypoint `chmod o+w database` when needed for WAL.
- Use `docker compose --profile assets run --rm node bash` then `npm install` / `npm run dev` or `npm run build` inside the container.
- Docker uses **PHP 8.2.30** (`docker/php/Dockerfile`, `composer.json` `config.platform.php`) so local FPM matches Hostinger-style 8.2.x. Run Composer with the same constraint (or use Docker) so the lock stays aligned with Symfony 7 / PHP 8.2.

## Production (cPanel / shared hosting)

- **No Node on the server**: run `npm run build` in CI or locally before upload. Vite writes versioned assets to `public/build/` (gitignored by default).
- Set `APP_URL` to the public site URL so generated links and assets resolve correctly.
- Map the host document root to Laravel’s `public/` (or symlink `public_html` → `public`). Keep application code **above** web root.
- MySQL on shared hosts often works best with `DB_HOST=127.0.0.1` (not `localhost`) and the port your host documents (sometimes not 3306).

## Inertia SSR vs Blade SEO

- `config/inertia.php`: SSR defaults favor **shared hosting** (`INERTIA_SSR_ENABLED` false by default). Enable SSR in Docker/local when you run `php artisan inertia:start-ssr` and set `INERTIA_SSR_URL`.
- Shared `seo` props are defined in `HandleInertiaRequests`; Blade duplicates critical `<meta>` / `canonical` for the initial HTML when SSR is off. Pages should also use `resources/js/Components/SeoHead.jsx` with `<Head>` for SPA navigations.

## Where code lives (public vs CMS backend)

- **Public site**: `routes/web.php` (top section), `app/Http/Controllers/Public/`, `resources/js/Pages/Public/`. URL `/` is named `home`.
- **CMS backend (staff)**: `routes/admin.php` (modules under `/admin/...`), `app/Http/Controllers/Admin/` (create as you add features), `resources/js/Pages/Admin/`. Main screen is `GET /admin` with Breeze route name `dashboard` (so login redirects still work). `GET /dashboard` redirects to `/admin`.
- **Auth**: `routes/auth.php`, `app/Http/Controllers/Auth/`, `resources/js/Pages/Auth/`.
- **Seeders**: `database/seeders/` (`Database\\Seeders` namespace). The PHP-FPM Docker entrypoint assigns the bind-mount owner to `database/migrations`, `database/seeders`, and `database/factories` so you can edit them on the host; only `database/database.sqlite` stays `www-data` for FPM writes. Run `php artisan db:seed` after `composer dump-autoload` if you changed autoload paths. Default admin: `admin@mail.com` / `password` (see `AdminUserSeeder`).

- Prefer explicit models: e.g. `Member`, `ElectionRecord` (bridge), `Session`, `Designation`. Eager-load in controllers before `Inertia::render`.
